---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About TSA Monster | Expert Product Reviews"
  description="TSA Monster publishes independent, hands-on product reviews to help you buy smarter. Learn about our editorial mission, review process, and team."
>
  <main class="flex-1 max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-slate max-w-none">
      <h1 class="font-display">About TSA Monster</h1>

      <p class="lead">
        TSA Monster exists to cut through the noise. We research, test, and write about the products
        that actually matter — so you spend less time second-guessing and more time living well.
      </p>

      <h2>Our Editorial Mission</h2>
      <p>
        We cover four categories: kitchen tools, outdoor gear, home essentials, and beauty products.
        In each of these spaces, the market is crowded with options, inflated claims, and sponsored
        "reviews" that are little more than advertisements in disguise. We think you deserve better.
      </p>
      <p>
        Every review we publish is written with a single question in mind: <em>would we recommend
        this to a friend?</em> If the answer is no, we say so — plainly, with specifics. If the
        answer is yes, we explain exactly why it earned that recommendation.
      </p>

      <h2>How We Review</h2>
      <p>
        Our review process is grounded in actual use. We don't base assessments on press releases or
        manufacturer spec sheets. Where possible, we test products hands-on — in real kitchens, on
        real trails, in real homes. For products we can't test ourselves, we aggregate long-term user
        feedback and cross-reference it with expert opinion and specification analysis.
      </p>
      <p>
        We look at:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Build quality and durability</strong> — does it hold up?</li>
        <li><strong>Performance against its stated purpose</strong> — does it do the thing?</li>
        <li><strong>Value</strong> — is the price justified by what you get?</li>
        <li><strong>Real-world usability</strong> — is it actually pleasant to use over time?</li>
        <li><strong>Comparison context</strong> — how does it stack up against obvious alternatives?</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Editorial Independence</h2>
      <p>
        TSA Monster participates in the Amazon Associates program, which means we may earn a small
        commission when you purchase a product through one of our links — at no additional cost to
        you. This affiliate relationship is disclosed prominently on every page and in our full
        <a href="/en/affiliate-disclosure/">Affiliate Disclosure</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        Affiliate income does not influence which products we review, which we recommend, or what we
        say about them. A product we don't believe in won't appear as a recommendation on this site,
        regardless of commission potential. Our credibility is worth more than any individual
        commission.
      </p>

      <h2>Who We Are</h2>
      <p>
        TSA Monster is a small, independent editorial team. We're not a big media company. We don't
        have a corporate mandate to fill a content quota. We write when we have something useful to
        say — and we take the time to say it properly.
      </p>
      <p>
        If you have a question about a review, want to flag an error, or have a product you think
        deserves coverage, we'd like to hear from you. Reach us at{' '}
        <a href="mailto:hello@tsa.monster">hello@tsa.monster</a>.
      </p>
    </article>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
